Definition: in an artful manner
Example: he craftily arranged to be there when the decision was announced; had ever circumstances conspired so cunningly?
Synonyms: adj, all, artful, crafty, cunningly, cunning, foxily, foxy, knavishly, knavish, slyly, sly, trickily, tricky, artfully, in, an, manner, he, arranged, to, be, there, when, the, decision, was, announced, had, ever, circumstances, conspired, so
Category: adv.all
